9:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What really happened in the Frozen Tower</span><hr size=1> If anyone heard anything about me about a Frozen Tower raid that I was invited to by my friend Baledin who is in Sons of Tao, this is what really happened.<br>
<br>
Ok, we went into Frozen Tower to get a wedding ring for a couple getting married. We only had one group of us. We got to floor 3 in about 2 hours. There, we encountered problems with those shadowed armored people.<br>
<br>
A few jumped us near the mirror entrance from the 2nd floor, but we were ok. Then we headed to the next mirror. 3 more attacked us and it got pretty bad. 3 of our group went down and the cleric, Baldin (warrior), and I were left getting attacked. Now, I know because they all told me this and I trust Baledin that the cleric said she was gunna camp then come back and rez us all. I didn't see this message because the spam coming from the 3 mobs hitting baledin and myself. I ran to her not knowing that she was camping trying to get a heal so that I wouldn't die. Then, I ran back the other way and gated luckily while one of the things were attacking me. When I had ran to her, they said that I trained one on her and she died along with the warrior not long after I gated.<br>
<br>
I gated to Freeport and walked to EC to see what was going on because we heard about a supposed event there. There wasn't one, but the lag was horrible. Now, it was time to go back and get corpses. They were getting help from some other people and asked to have one person to disband. I disbanded and then went LD from the bad lag in EC. I tried to log back into EQ for about 15min, but it wasn't working, so I gave up. They all think that I camped because I didn't want to help clean up the corpses, but if you know me, I wouldn't do that; come on.<br>
<br>
That's what really happened. I'm really not an evil guy.<br>
40th Magician <p><b>K</b>nobb <b>K</b>nokker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufarfus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>farfus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/26/01 6:56:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I understand</span><hr size=1> I had occasionally had things like that happen.  A year ago i was going ld all the time so basically anytime i grouped i was in trouble.  But if you were that close to the zone, everybody shoulda zoned quick, including the cleric.  So personally i wouldnt be too concerned.  Of course i dont play EQ anymore so i really am not concerned. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/upurtyogre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>purtyogre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/26/01 7:39:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.swordsofhonor.com/lib/greatsword/warrior WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I understand</span><hr size=1> the zone out on that floor isn't the same as the zone in though, is it?<br>
