 to drag his corpse.  I could not find it in the hall.  I was mad then.... no, mad doesn't even begin to describe the rage I felt.  If He had paid attention he would have realized that the person being asked to leave the group was my EQ husband who was in the group so that we could continue to keep the group together.  The bottom line of this entire fiasco is that it wasn't just one person's fault that it went bad.  It was my fault for a bad pull, and Knobb's fault for not paying attention to his screen.  It goes to show that communication is essential during a high level raid and the cleric needs to camp out when they say so....   I just wanted to give my 2cp about the situation.  I truly don't think you are a bad guy Knobb.<br>
<br>
Grenoya Boncoeur<br>
